General.Name: Systemair AB
General.Description: Systemair AB (publ), a ventilation company, engages in the manufacture and sale of ventilation products in Europe, North America, the Middle East, Asia, Australia, Africa, and internationally. The company offers heating products, including convectors, controls, ceiling fans, radiant and fan heaters; fans and accessories, such as duct, roof, axial, explosion proof, domestic, smoke extract, jet, and other fans, as well as electrical and mechanical accessories for ventilation and fans for aggressive media; and residential ventilation systems comprising residential fans, heat pumps and multi-units geothermal systems, cooker hoods, diffuse and air valves, ducts, grillers, vacuum systems, accessories, and filters. It also provides fire safety products that include fire and smoke control dampers; air distribution products consisting of grilles, air volume controls, diffusers, and external louvers; air handling units, including compact and modular AHUs, roof ventilation units, and compact and modular AHU accessories; air conditioning systems, such as chillers and heat pumps, rooftop units, fan coil units, water source heat pumps, close control units, split systems, VRF systems, and accessories; and commercial, industrial, cold storage, revolving door, and control for air curtains, as well as accessories. The company's products are used in homes, offices, factories, hospitals, swimming pools, multi-storey car parks, and airports, as well as data centers, schools and office and public spaces, infrastructure and transport, industrial and workshop premises, and hotel and entertainment sectors. It sells its products to ventilation contractors and distributors under the Systemair, Frico, Fantech, and Menerga brand names. Systemair AB (publ) was incorporated in 1972 and is headquartered in Skinnskatteberg, Sweden.
